         <abstract>
            <p>Any imaginary cyclic quartic field can be expressed uniquely in the form $K = Q(\sqrt{A(D + B\sqrt D)})$, where $A$ is squarefree, odd and negative, $D = B^2 + C^2$ is squarefree, $B &gt; 0, C &gt; 0$, and $(A, D) = 1$. Explicit formulae for the discriminant and conductor of $K$ are given in terms of $A, B, C, D$. The calculation of tables of the class numbers $h(K)$ of such fields $K$ is described.</p>
          </abstract>
